Jeanette Chabalala, News24 (File, AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Five armed robbers targeted the Beverly jewellery store at the Pavilion in Durban on Wednesday night, KwaZulu-Natal police said."Five unknown men wearing balaclavas entered the jewellery shop at 18:00 and demanded money. No money was found so they took jewellery," Lieutenant Nqobile Gwala said.&nbsp;Gwala said when the men left the store they fired shots at security guards, however no one was injured. &nbsp;The men fled the scene in a white Volkswagen Touran. Gwala said the suspects were still at large. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.